Class 7

switch on of the conditional statements that is used to execute 1 statement from multiple conditions

can be used instead of multiple else if (with limitations)

switch(variable){
	
	case valueForVariable: 
		code;
		break;
	case valueForVariable:
		code;
		break;
	default:
		code:
}

Cases cannot be duplicate

Cannot use relatonal or Logical Operators

int num1=10;
int num2=12;

if(num1>num2){
	SOPln("Num 1 is larger")
}

Datatypes allowed in switch --> byte, short, int, char, String

int age=5;
String human;

if (age==1){
	human="Baby";
}else if(age==3){
	human="Child";
}

switch(age){
	
	case 1: 
		human="Baby";
		break;
	case 3:
		human="Child";
		break;
}

which is true?
1. Every switch can be written using else if --> true
2. Every else if can be wtitten using switch --> false

Incremnet & decrement opearators used with variables ++ or -- and this operators will be used with LOOPs statements

LOOPs is Java - execute block of code multiple times

Loops:
	while
	do while
	for
	enhanced for loop/ advanced for loop/ for each loop

System.out.println("Good morning");
System.out.println("Good morning");
System.out.println("Good morning");
System.out.println("Good morning");
System.out.println("Good morning");


int time=10;

if(time<12){
	System.out.println("Good morning");
}

while(time<12){
	System.out.println("Good morning");
}

while(time<=12){ --> condition will be true 3 times
		System.out.println("Good morning");
		time++;
}

initialize a variable

while(test variable --> true){
	code;
	increment or decrement;
}

boolean rain=true;

if(rain){
	SOPln("Take umbrella");//1 time
}

while(rain){
	SOPln("Take umbrella");//infinite
}

while(rain){
	SOPln("Take umbrella");//1 time
	rain=false;
}
------------------------
do while loop repeats block of code as long as a condtionis true

int num1=11;
		
do {
	System.out.println("Hello");
	num1++;
	
}while(num1<=5);

vs while

int num=11;
		
while(num<=5) {
	System.out.println("Hello");
	num++;
}

do while vs while?
do while first executes code and then tests the condtion
while checks condition first and then executes block of code;

When to use while or do while is BEST choice to use --> When we do not know how many times we have to repeat block of code

When you know how many times you want to repeat block of code --> 
for loop is a best choice

using while;

int a=1; --> declare variable

while(a<4){ --> test condition
	code;
	code;
	code;
	code;
	code;
	code;
	a++; --> increment
}

for(int b=1;b<4;b++ ){
	code;
}









